":"to knock, rap, strike; to cudgel, to driveback with a stick","tags":["ambitransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to knock, rap, strike; to beat the drum, to ring, to clink","tags":["ambitransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reproach, to impugn the character of","tags":["ambitransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover (a mare) (of a stallion)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cast lots","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be the winner in casting lots","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ring, to jingle","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to creak, to crunch","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to creak, to crunch; to itch, to cause remorse","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to accept advice"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to conquer in throwing the javelin or spear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be empty, deserted, bare","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be empty, deserted, bare; to be bald","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cuss, to reprimand","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to percuss, to ring, to drum","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَرَعَ (qaraʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَرِعَ (qariʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"button, pustule, itch, rash","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"لحب القرع والديدان الكبير\nسرخس وبرنج وقنبيل وتربذ وترمس ومر متساوية الشربة أربعة دراهم بماء حار","english":"For (the treatment of ) flukes and large worms\nMale fern, embelia, kamala, turpeth, lupine, and myrrh (in) equal (parts). A potion (may be made by using) four dirham (of it) with hot water."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pumpkin, gourd","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chemical retort","tags":["archaic","collective"],"examples":[{"text":"القَرْع، والأَنْبِيق، وهما آلتا صُنَّاع ماء الوَرْد. والسفلى هي القرع، والعليا على هيئة المِحْجمة، هي الأنبيق.","english":"The retort and the still are two implements of those who make rose-water. The lower is the retort, the upper of the shape of a cupping glass, that is the still."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From ق ر ع (q r ʕ), ranging in semantics from casting lots and sortition with sticks or arrow-shafts to casting the whip and otherwise preceding rough.\n\nFrom Classical Syriac ܩܪܐܐ (qarrʾā)."},"ipa":null}